y stabbing]]\n|April 14, 2014\n|[[Calgary, Alberta]]\n|5\n| Knife\n| No\n|22-year old Matthew de Grood fatally stabbed five people at a party. He was subsequently found Not Criminally Responsible on Account of Mental Disorder on 5 counts of First Degree Murder.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://globalnews.ca/news/2720276/decision-expected-in-trial-of-accused-brentwood-murderer-matthew-de-grood/|title=Matthew de Grood found not criminally responsible in Brentwood murders|work=Global News|access-date=March 6, 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Western Forest Products#2014 Nanaimo Shooting|2014 Nanaimo Shooting]]\n|April 30, 2014\n|[[Nanaimo]], [[British Columbia]]\n|2\n| Long gun\n| \n|A former employee opened fire with a shotgun at a Western Forest Products mill, killing two employees and wounding two others.\n|-\n|[[Moncton shooting]]\n|June 4, 2014\n|[[Moncton]], [[New Brunswick]]\n|3\n| Long gun\n| No\n|24-year-old from Moncton, shot five armed officers from the Royal Canadian Mounted Police (RCMP), killing three and severely injuring two.<ref>{{cite web|title=Moncton shootings: 3 RCMP officers dead, 2 wounded|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/new-brunswick/moncton-shootings-3-rcmp-officers-dead-2-wounded-1.2665359|website=CBC|accessdate=October 24, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[2014 Edmonton killings]] \n|December 29, 2014\n|[[Edmonton, Alberta]]\n|8\n|\n| Yes\n| 53-year-old Phu Lam shot and killed 7 in one Edmonton residence, then went to a home in south Edmonton where he killed Cyndi Duong because he found he was raising a child that was not biologically his own. Phu Lam was found the next day after committing suicide in Fort Saskatchewan.\n|-\n|[[La Loche shootings]]\n|January 22, 2016\n|[[La Loche]], [[Saskatchewan]]\n| 4 / 7\n| Long gun\n| No\n|A 17-year-old student, whose identity is protected by youth justice publication ban, convicted of killing two of his cousins at their home, then going to [[La Loche Community School]] and continued firing, killing a teacher and an assistant, and wounding seven others. School Shooting.<ref>https://globalnews.ca/news/6110038/adult-sentence-upheld-in-la-loche-school-shooter-appeal/</ref>\n|-\n|[[Scarborough crossbow attack]]\n|August 25, 2016\n|[[Scarborough, Toronto|Scarborough]], [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]]\n|3\n| Crossbow\n| No\n|35-year-old Brett Ryan<ref>{{cite web|title=Man charged in Toronto crossbow killings is a convicted bank robber|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/crossbow-scarborough-deaths-1.3736694|website=cbc.ca|publisher=CBC|accessdate=August 26, 2016}}</ref> killed 3 people and wounded 2 others with a crossbow before being apprehended by police.\n|-\n|[[Quebec City mosque shooting]]\n|January 29, 2017\n|[[Quebec City]], [[Quebec]]\n| 6\n| Handgun\n| No\n| [[Quebec City mosque shooting#Perpetrator|Alexandre Bissonnette]] (a former [[University of Laval]] student) killed 6 people and wounded 18 others at the [[Islamic Cultural Centre of Quebec City]].<ref>{{cite news|title=6 dead, 2 arrested after shooting at Quebec City mosque|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/montreal/quebec-city-mosque-gun-shots-1.3957686|accessdate=January 30, 2017|agency=Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|date=January 20, 2017|language=English}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Toronto van attack]]\n|April 23, 2018\n|[[North York]], [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]]\n|10\n| Vehicle\n| No\n| Single driver, Alek Minassian killed 10 people and wounded 15 others in a [[vehicle-ramming attack]] at Yonge Street, North York City Centre.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/pedestrians-struck-white-van-1.4631564|title=9 dead, 16 injured after van strikes pedestrians in North York|work=[[CBC News]]|date=April 23, 2018|access-date=April 23, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Danforth shooting]]\n|July 22, 2018\n|[[Greektown, Toronto]]\n|3 (including the gunman)\n| Hand gun\n| Yes\n|The 29-year-old gunman, Faisal Hussain, shot 10 people before fatally shooting himself. An 18-year-old woman was pronounced dead after she was taken to the hospital from gunshot wounds, and a critically injured 10-year-old girl was also pronounced dead after being taken to hospital.<ref name=\"globe\">{{cite news|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/canada/toronto/article-one-dead-13-injured-gunman-killed-in-toronto-mass-shooting/|title=Three dead, including shooter, 12 injured in Toronto mass shooting}}</ref>\"\n|-\n|[[Fredericton shooting]]\n|August 10, 2018\n|[[Fredericton, New Brunswick]]\n| 4\n| Long gun\n| No\n|48-year-old accused, Matthew Vincent Raymond, shot 4 people, 2 civilians Bobbie-Lee Wright and Donnie Robichaud, along with officers Robb Costello and Sara Burns.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/new-brunswick/matthew-raymond-fredericton-police-murder-trial-1.5064326|title=Accused Fredericton shooter Matthew Raymond will stand trial Sept. 30}}</ref>\n|-\n|Salmon Arm Church of Christ shooting\n|April 14, 2019\n|[[Salmon Arm]], [[British Columbia]]\n|1 / 1 / 0\n| Shooting\n|No\n|Matrix Savage Gathergood, 25, was charged with first-degree murder of Gordon Parmenter, aggravated assault and disguise with intent to commit an indictable offence in connection with the shooting on April 15.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/salmon-arm-shooting-charges-1.5098750|title=25-year-old charged with murder after deadly shooting at Salmon Arm church|last=|first=|date=April 15, 2019|website=CBC|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190522170801/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/salmon-arm-shooting-charges-1.5098750|archive-date=May 22, 2019|access-date=January 26, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|Penticton shootings\n|April 15, 2019\n|[[Penticton]], [[British Columbia]]\n|4\n| Long gun\n| No\n|Four people killed in three different locations by a man reported to have used a rifle, and who immediately turned himself in to police.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://vancouversun.com/news/local-news/penticton-shootings-live-updates-and-what-we-know-so-far |title = Penticton shootings: Live updates and what we know so far &#124; Vancouver Sun|date = April 17, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[2019 Northern British Columbia murders]]\n|July 14-19, 2019\n|[[British Columbia]]\n|3\n| Long gun\n| Yes\n|An Australian and an American tourist were found dead. Five days later, another man was found dead.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.insider.com/british-columbia-murders-missing-teens-link-rcmp-2019-7 |title = 2 murders, a death, and 2 disappearances in a remote, wild part of Canada could all be connected, police say}}</ref> On July 23, the RCMP initiated a country-wide manhunt for the two outstanding suspects.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nationalpost.com/news/canada/ten-days-four-provinces-how-two-b-c-suspected-fugitives-continue-to-evade-rcmp|title=Ten days, four provinces: How two B.C. fugitives continue to evade RCMP {{!}} National Post|last=News|last2=Canada|date=2019-07-29|language=en-CA|access-date=2019-07-30}}</ref> On August 7, two bodies, later identified as the suspects, were found in dense brush near the [[Nelson River]] in [[Manitoba]]. Autopsies and press conference reported death by suicide.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/manitoba/rcmp-significant-announcement-1.5239053|title=Bodies found in northern Manitoba believed to be 2 B.C. fugitives: RCMP|last=Glowacki |first=Laura|date=August 7, 2019|work=[[CBC News]]|access-date=August 7, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[2019 Markham home massacre]]\n|July 28, 2019\n|[[Markham, Ontario]]\n| 4\n| Knife\n| No\n|23-year-old Menhaz Zaman is charged after allegedly killing four family members by cutting their throats in a Markham home.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://toronto.citynews.ca/2019/07/28/four-bodies-found-in-markham-ont-home-one-man-in-custody/ | title=Four bodies found in Markham, Ont., home; one man in custody}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of conflicts in Canada]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}{{massacres}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:M}}\n[[Category:Lists of massacres by country|Canada]]\n[[Category:Canada history-related lists|massacres]]\n[[Category:Massacres in Canada| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of disasters in Canada]]\n", "name_user": "MGHuc", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eList", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_massacres_in_Canada"}
