ingdon-on-Thames|Abingdon]] |isbn=978-1-1345-5976-3 |ref=harv|author-link=James Allan Stewart Evans}}\n*{{cite book|last1=Freely|first1=John|last2=\u00c7akmak|first2=Ahmet S.|title=Byzantine Monuments of Istanbul|date=2004|publisher=[[Cambridge University Press]]|location=New York|isbn=978-0-5211-7905-8|ref=harv|author-link1=John Freely}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Friell|first1=Gerard|last2=Williams|first2=Stephen|title=The Rome that Did Not Fall: The Survival of the East in the Fifth Century|date=2005|publisher=[[Routledge]]|isbn=978-1-1347-3546-4|ref=harv|location= [[Hoboken, New Jersey|Hoboken]]}}\n* {{cite book|last1=Jeffreys|first1=Elizabeth|last2=Haldon|first2=John|last3=Cormack|first3=Robin|title=The Oxford Handbook of Byzantine Studies|date=2008|publisher=[[Oxford University Press]]|isbn=978-0-1992-5246-6|ref=harv|location=Oxford|authorlink1=Elizabeth Jeffreys|authorlink3=Robin Cormack|contributor-last=Gallagher|contributor-first=Clarence|contribution=The Two Churches}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Grant |first1=Michael |title=The Roman Emperors: A Biographical Guide to the Rulers of Imperial Rome 31 BC \u2013 AD 476 |date=1985 |publisher=[[Scribner's]] |isbn=978-0684183886 |ref=harv |location=New York |author-link=Michael Grant (author, born 1954) |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/romanemperorsbio0000gran }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Gregory |first1=Timothy E. |title=The Oxford Dictionary of Byzantium|date=1991 |isbn= 978-0-1951-8792-2|editor1-last=Kazhdan|editor1-first=Alexander Petrovich|ref=harv|location=[[Oxford]]|author-link1=Timothy E. Gregory|author-link2=Alexander Kazhdan|doi=10.1093/acref/9780195046526.001.0001|publisher=[[Oxford University Press]]}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Christophilopoulou |first1=Aikaterin\u0113 |title=Byzantine History |date=1986 |publisher=A. M. Hakkert |isbn=9789025608361 |ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book |last1=Head |first1=Constance |title=Imperial Byzantine Portraits: A Verbal and Graphic Gallery |date=1982 |publisher=Univers